						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged. It seems to record an endowment of land (a <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> and half in extent) by a resident of Tañjāvūr to the temple of Tiruviḍaimuruduḍaiyār, for offering and worship to goddess Paḷḷikkaṭṭil-Pirāṭṭiyār. The <hi rend="italic">dēvakarmis</hi> of the temple the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Tiraimūr, the <hi rend="italic">Nagarattār</hi> of Tiruviḍai-marudil and the <hi rend="italic">Śrikāryam</hi> (supervisor) are stated to have met in the big <hi rend="italic">kāvaṇam</hi> (courtyard) of the temple when the gift was made.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
